description.plain:
Portugal. The Man is an American rock band based in Portland, Oregon. The group currently consists of John Gourley, Zach Carothers, Kyle O'Quin, Jason Sechrist, Eric Howk, and Zoe Manville.

Gourley and Carothers met and began playing music together in high school in Wasilla, Alaska. Since the formation of Portugal. The Man in 2005, the band has released eight studio albums and three EPs. Their first two albums were released on Fearless Records. They also released material on their own imprint Approaching AIRballoons through indie label Equal Vision Records. On April 2, 2010, the band signed to Atlantic Records.

The band announced an upcoming album titled Gloomin' + Doomin' in February of 2016. The album was later scrapped due to complications and thus, Woodstock was born, their eighth and most-successful full-length studio album.



“Feel It Still” reached the mainstream and, for the first time, Portugal. The Man entered the Billboard’s Hot 100, achieving No. 4. The song also won a Grammy for “Best Pop Duo/Group Performance.”



Current Members:

John Gourley: vocals, guitar (2004–present)
Zachary Carothers: bass guitar, backing vocals (2004–present)
Kyle O'Quin: keyboards, synthesizers, guitar, backing vocals (2007, 2012–present)
Eric Howk: guitar (2015–present)
Jason Sechrist: drums (2005–09, 2009–11, 2014–2015, 2016–present)
Zoe Manville: ongoing involvement

Former Members:

Ryan Neighbors: keyboards, synthesizers, backing vocals
Kane Ritchotte: drums, percussion, backing vocals
Wesley Hubbard: keyboards
Noah Gersh: guitar, vocals, miscellaneous percussion
Nick Klein: guitar
Harvey Tumbleson: beats
Garrett Lunceford: drums
Matt Price: guitar, keyboards

songs.full_title: Live in the Moment by Portugal. The Man
songs.title: Live in the Moment

description.plain:
“Live in the Moment” is the third single release from their 2017 album Woodstock and it talks about enjoying things in the present. The song is also featured on the 2017 released football game FIFA 18 from EA Sports Canada.

‘Live in the moment’ is such a common, well-known phrase—everybody’s heard that before. I love the idea of trying to give something like that new life. It looks easy until you hear it in your context, and you see the bigger picture.

—John Baldwin Gourley, Songwriter Universe

description.plain:
“So Young” was the 3rd single released by Portugal. The Man ahead of their album Woodstock, which dropped June 16th, 2017.  Featuring spoken recordings from Zoe Manville and A$AP Rocky, lead singer John Gourley is also backed up by Zoe on the choruses.

[that song] is just us being a band, sitting in a room and jamming. That’s the reason it made it [on] Woodstock.

—John Gourley, Billboard
